abstract: United States Geological Survey reports 6.2 magnitude earthquake, centered in Hindu Kush region of Afghanistan, that impacted parts of northwest Pakistan as well.
lead_paragraph: More than 30 people were injured as houses or walls collapsed in the northwestern Pakistan city of Peshawar.

headline.print_headline: Asia; Quake Rattles Pakistan and Afghanistan
